tence\": \"The tradition of giving a bronze, silver or gold medal to the winning athletes of every event began at the St. Louis Olympic Games in 1904.\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tradition\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze, silver or gold medal\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"the winning athletes\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"every event\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 461}, {\"ngram\": \"the St. Louis Olympic Games\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the materials largely remain the same, the design of the medals changes for every Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the materials\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 564}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 578}, {\"ngram\": \"every Olympic Games\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is because the host city is allowed to choose the design of the medals for the year that the event is held in their country.\", \"from\": 612, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the host city\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris Olympics 2024 So, what exactly are Olympic medal made from - and how much do they weigh?\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic medal\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC) guidelines state that gold medals should contain at least six grams of 24 carat gold coating, with the rest made up of silver.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"at least six grams\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"24 carat gold coating\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver medals are made up of silver, whilst bronze medals consist of copper, zinc, tin, and small traces of silver.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Silver medals\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1071}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze medals\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"copper\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1133}, {\"ngram\": \"zinc\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"tin\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"small traces\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each Olympic medal on offer in Paris also contain original iron from the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.99999999997749, \"rank\": 2.2496882252585972e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"offer\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"original iron\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Iron components have been permanently removed from the tower during reconstruction work over the years.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Iron components\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"reconstruction work\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1350}, {\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals feature the iron as hexagons in the middle of the designs - the geometrical shape of France.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1464, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6750190870583146, \"rank\": 0.4711298193488726, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medals\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1378}, {\"ngram\": \"the iron\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"hexagons\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1421}, {\"ngram\": \"the designs\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"the geometrical shape\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Explaining the design on the official Olympic website, the Games state: 'This symbol is a reminder of the whole nation's engagement in delivering an historic Olympic and Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"the official Olympic website\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1526}, {\"ngram\": \"This symbol\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"a reminder\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1571}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole nation's engagement\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"an historic Olympic and Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Stripped of its \\\"Eiffel Tower brown\\\" paint, the iron is returned to its original colour.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its \\\"Eiffel Tower brown\\\" paint\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"the iron\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"its original colour\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Placed in the centre and imprinted with the emblem of the Paris 2024 Games, this piece of heritage fits perfectly within the gold, silver and bronze core of the medal.'\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"the emblem\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1802}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Games\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"this piece\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"heritage\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1850}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold, silver and bronze core\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1905}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the design of the medals changes for every Olympic Games, the International Olympic Committee regulations stipulate that all medals must include the Olympic five rings symbol; Nike, the Greek goddess of victory, in front of the Panathinaikos Stadium and the official name of the respective Games somewhere in the design.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 2024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Internatio